com.camerontec.catalys.core.session.event

Interface ISessionStatusListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SampleMonitor, SessionStatusListenerBase

    public interface ISessionStatusListener
    This is a listener to Session status events once they have been split out into method calls. This is sometimes a more convenient way to process Session status events.

    The SessionStatusEventRouter takes a Session status event and then calls associated methods of a supplied listener supporting this interface.

      • onInMessageDecrypted

        void onInMessageDecrypted(CatalysEventObject event,
                          IFIXMessage message)
        Called whenever a message has been decrypted.

        NOTE:
        This should NOT be used to retrieve a message for processing. It is intended to simply signal that a message has arrived. Messages should be retrieved using the Session's getMessage method. This will ensure that messages are processed in the correct order and are correctly removed from the internal application queue.

        Parameters:
        event - Event which triggered this callback
        message - Decrypted message.

      • onInMessageReceived

        void onInMessageReceived(CatalysEventObject event,
                         Object receivedData)
        Called when a message is first received.

        The form in which the message is received will depend on the underlying transport. For a stream based transport such as Socket's, the raw message will be in the form of an array of bytes (byte[]). For a message based transport, the message may already be in the form of a Message object.

        NOTE:
        This should NOT be used to retrieve a message for processing. It is intended to simply signal that a message has arrived. Messages should be retrieved using the Session's getMessage method. This will ensure that messages are processed in the correct order and are correctly removed from the internal application queue.

        Parameters:
        event - Event which triggered this callback
        receivedData - The raw, encrypted, message in whatever form it is received.

      • onLoggedOnStatusChange

        void onLoggedOnStatusChange(CatalysEventObject event,
                            int logonEventType,
                            IFIXMessage fixMessage,
                            boolean externalRequest,
                            boolean isLoggedOn,
                            IConnectionPoint connectionPoint,
                            Connection connection,
                            String textMessage)
        Called when the logged on status of the session changes.

        This replaces the old, deprecated, loggedOnStatus method which had an IParty parameter in place of the new IConnectionPoint parameter. The IConnectionPoint object holds both parties involved. The party object passed in the old method can be obtained by calling the getExternalParty method on the IConnectionPoint object.

        Parameters:
        event - the associated event
        logonEventType - Indicates the type of log on status change. See LoggedOnStatusEvent for the valid logon event types.
        fixMessage - Associated FIX message if any. ie Logon or logout message.
        externalRequest - True if this event is the result of an externally received Logon or Logoff request.
        isLoggedOn - True if session is logged on following this event.
        connectionPoint - Connection point associated with the session at the time of this event.
        connection - Connection associated with the session at the time of this event.
        textMessage - Text message associated with this event - for example a log out reason.

      • onOutMessageAboutToSend

        void onOutMessageAboutToSend(CatalysEventObject event,
                             IFIXMessage message,
                             Object sentData)
        Called just before a message is sent.

        The form in which the message is sent will depend on the underlying transport. For a stream based transport such as Socket's, the message will be in the form of an array of bytes (byte[]).

        Parameters:
        event - Event which triggered this callback
        message - The unencrypted message.
        sentData - The encrypted data actually to be sent.

      • onResendStatusChange

        void onResendStatusChange(CatalysEventObject event,
                          boolean completed,
                          int beginSeq,
                          int endSeq)
        Called whenever the Session is resending messages.

        Called once at the start of the resend and once when the resend is complete.

        Parameters:
        event - Event which triggered this callback
        completed - If false the resend has just started, otherwise it has completed.
        beginSeq - Sequence number of first message being resent.
        endSeq - Sequence number of last message to be resent.
